---
const findings = [
  {
    title: 'Domain-specific knowledge graphs win on structured corpora',
    body: 'Across the LightRAG benchmark suite, graph-augmented retrieval substantially outperforms naive vector search on regulatory and legal text — the closest analogs to our corpus.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Hierarchical norm resolution yields legally consistent answers',
    body: 'Encoding lex specialis directly into the retrieval layer ensures that the more specific lower-level norm is preferred when rules conflict.',
  },
  {
    title: 'A dual-LLM split balances cost, latency, and quality',
    body: 'Costly graph construction is decoupled from latency-critical query answering — each LLM is chosen for the constraint that matters most at that stage.',
  },
];
---

<section id="conclusion" class="section-pad">
  <div class="container-wide">
    <!-- Section masthead -->
    <div class="reveal grid grid-cols-12 gap-6 border-b border-ink pb-8">
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-3">
        <div class="section-mark">06 — Conclusion</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-9">
        <h2 class="display-lg">
          Why graph-based RAG wins.
        </h2>
        <p class="body-lg mt-6">
          The proposed system effectively retrieves and synthesizes Turkish
          academic regulations across three hierarchical levels using
          graph-based RAG. The dual-LLM architecture balances cost, latency,
          and quality, while hierarchical norm resolution ensures legally
          consistent responses. Results confirm that domain-specific
          knowledge-graph construction <span class="text-ink font-semibold">substantially outperforms</span>
          naive vector search for structured regulatory corpora.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Findings -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3">
      {findings.map((f, i) => (
        <div class={`reveal border-b border-rule p-8 md:py-12 md:px-10 ${i < 2 ? 'md:border-r' : ''}`} style={`transition-delay: ${i * 100}ms`}>
          <div class="font-mono tabular text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-brand">
            Finding {String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}
          </div>
          <h3 class="mt-5 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-ink leading-snug">
            {f.title}
          </h3>
          <p class="marginalia mt-3">{f.body}</p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
